The Nigerian Air Force has postponed entrance examinations into Air Force Military School (AFMS) and Air Force Girls Military School (AFGMS) Jos. The entrance examinations which was scheduled for 4 April 2020 has now been tentatively fixed for 16 May 2020. A statement by the Director of Public Relations and Information Air Commodore Ibikunle Daramola said the postponement was in compliance with precautions aimed at curbing the spread of COVID-19. “This is to inform parents/guardians of candidates that applied for admission into the Air Force Military School (AFMS) and Air Force Girls’ Military School (AFGMS) Jos that the entrance examination, which was earlier scheduled for 4 April 2020, has now been tentatively rescheduled to hold on 16 May 2020 in compliance with precautions aimed at curbing the spread of COVID-19,” he said